subject: Golf
lead_paragraph: Lorena Ochoa had eight birdies but finished with two bogeys in shooting a 66 yesterday to take a one-stroke lead over Sophie Gustafson entering the final round of the L.P.G.A. Safeway Classic in Portland, Ore. Ochoa is at 11-under 133 after two rounds at Columbia Edgewater County Club. Gustafson, who shared the lead after the first round with Ji-Young Oh, was one shot back after a 68. Oh was third, four shots back.
